        <h1>HTML Hyperlinks Demonstration</h1>
        <p>Hyperlinks in HTML are created using the <code>< a ></code> tag with the <code>href</code> attribute to specify the link destination. The <code>target</code> attribute determines how the link is opened.</p> 
        <h3>Basic Hyperlink</h3>
        <p>Visit the <a href="https://www.google.com">Google</a> website. (Opens in the same tab.)</p>
        <h3>Open Link in a New Tab</h3>
        <p>Visit the <a href="https://www.wikipedia.org" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a> website. (Opens in a new tab.)</p>
        <h3>Open Link in Parent Frame</h3>
        <p>If the page is inside a frame, visit <a href="https://www.example.com" target="_parent">Example</a> in the parent frame.</p>
        <h3>Open Link in Full Window</h3>
        <p>Visit <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news" target="_top">BBC News</a> to load in the full browser window.</p>
    </body>
